                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>A facsimile of this inscription was kindly forwarded to me by Mr. Rāghavendrāchārya of Vānūr. It consists of one Sanskrit verse, which is identical with the last verse of <hi rend="bold">Rājasiṁha's</hi> large inscription at <hi rend="bold">Kañchī</hi> (<ref target="DHARMA_INSSIIv01p0i0024">No. 24</ref>, above). Hence it may be concluded, that the Panamalai Cave was founded by Rājasiṁha and that in his time the <hi rend="bold">Pallavas</hi> ruled as far south as Panamalai.</p>						
                            
                        </summary>
                    </msContents>
